to share these ideas.

00:01:11.230 --> 00:01:13.450 align:middle line:84%
Well, I have a
passion for what I

00:01:13.450 --> 00:01:16.790 align:middle line:84%
call the deep awake state, for
this awakening that can happen.

00:01:16.790 --> 00:01:18.420 align:middle line:84%
It seems it's
completely natural.

00:01:18.420 --> 00:01:20.010 align:middle line:90%
It's available to everyone.

00:01:20.010 --> 00:01:22.970 align:middle line:84%
And I would just like as
many people as possible

00:01:22.970 --> 00:01:25.540 align:middle line:84%
to experience it and to
share it with other people.

00:01:25.540 --> 00:01:27.360 align:middle line:84%
So the opportunity
to share ideas

00:01:27.360 --> 00:01:29.980 align:middle line:84%
about which I have
passion is something

00:01:29.980 --> 00:01:32.100 align:middle line:90%
to be embraced, so thank you.

00:01:32.100 --> 00:01:34.430 align:middle line:84%
Tell us, why are we
here at this cemetery?

00:01:34.430 --> 00:01:37.740 align:middle line:84%
Because there's a little--
life brought us here, honestly.

00:01:37.740 --> 00:01:40.360 align:middle line:10%
It wasn't like
everything was planned.

00:01:40.360 --> 00:01:43.700 align:middle line:84%
But there's a little
thing for you here.

00:01:43.700 --> 00:01:46.120 align:middle line:84%
Well, I spend a fair amount
of time in cemeteries.

00:01:46.120 --> 00:01:47.251 align:middle line:90%
It's a very sobering place.

00:01:47.251 --> 00:01:48.950 align:middle line:84%
It's a good place to walk,
if you're a philosopher,

00:01:48.950 --> 00:01:52.674 align:middle line:84%
and think, and to realize
how precious life is.

00:01:52.674 --> 00:01:53.840 align:middle line:84%
Because you're
surrounded by death.

00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:56.015 align:middle line:84%
And you're also surrounded
by the mystery of existence,

00:01:56.015 --> 00:01:59.100 align:middle line:84%
that you are on this journey
between the beginning

00:01:59.100 --> 00:02:01.950 align:middle line:84%
of your life and what is
coming, the end of your life.

00:02:01.950 --> 00:02:04.070 align:middle line:10%
And I worked with
people who were dying

00:02:04.070 --> 00:02:08.370 align:middle line:10%
at one point in my life
for the same reason,

00:02:08.370 --> 00:02:10.960 align:middle line:10%
partly because I wanted
to give something, express

00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:14.930 align:middle line:10%
my love of others and be
there in people's distress,

00:02:14.930 --> 00:02:20.320 align:middle line:10%
but also because coming face
to face with the end of life,

00:02:20.320 --> 00:02:24.910 align:middle line:10%
I think, can cast great
light on life itself.

00:02:24.910 --> 00:02:28.000 align:middle line:84%
Plato, Socrates-- one of my
heroes, philosophical heroes,

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:30.890 align:middle line:84%
said the whole of philosophy
is a meditation on death.

00:02:30.890 --> 00:02:33.440 align:middle line:84%
And in some ways, I
think that's true.

00:02:33.440 --> 00:02:34.640 align:middle line:84%
I've just finished
making a movie,

00:02:34.640 --> 00:02:36.770 align:middle line:84%
which starts in a graveyard
for that very reason.

00:02:36.770 --> 00:02:39.130 align:middle line:84%
It's like if we can-- it
feels like, like let's

00:02:39.130 --> 00:02:40.390 align:middle line:90%
get to the heart of things.

00:02:40.390 --> 00:02:41.090 align:middle line:90%
We're alive.

00:02:41.090 --> 00:02:42.530 align:middle line:90%
We don't know what it is.

00:02:42.530 --> 00:02:43.270 align:middle line:90%
We're going to die.

00:02:43.270 --> 00:02:44.840 align:middle line:90%
We don't know what that is.

00:02:44.840 --> 00:02:46.170 align:middle line:84%
Now what are we
going to do about it?

00:02:46.170 --> 00:02:47.130 align:middle line:90%
It's part of the mystery.

00:02:47.130 --> 00:02:49.120 align:middle line:10%
So we'll go back
later on about this,

00:02:49.120 --> 00:02:51.370 align:middle line:10%
but first I would love to
hear-- I know you bring

00:02:51.370 --> 00:02:53.560 align:middle line:10%
some scientific
proof, and you bridge

00:02:53.560 --> 00:02:57.130 align:middle line:10%
science with spirituality,
and that's an important part.

00:02:57.130 --> 00:02:59.590 align:middle line:10%
Could you tell us
what kind of science

00:02:59.590 --> 00:03:00.820 align:middle line:10%
are we talking about here?

00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:03.200 align:middle line:10%
And how do you bridge
that in your books

00:03:03.200 --> 00:03:04.950 align:middle line:10%
and in your workshops?

00:03:04.950 --> 00:03:09.430 align:middle line:84%
Well, "The Mystery Experience,"
my new book, the subtitle

00:03:09.430 --> 00:03:13.590 align:middle line:84%
is "A Revolutionary Approach
to Spiritual Awakening."

00:03:13.590 --> 00:03:18.270 align:middle line:84%
And why I felt the need to try
and do that was, after having

00:03:18.270 --> 00:03:20.510 align:middle line:84%
written all of these books on
different spiritual traditions,

00:03:20.510 --> 00:03:23.970 align:middle line:84%
studying what they were
saying, trying to translate

00:03:23.970 --> 00:03:28.420 align:middle line:84%
these often-ancient ideas into
an idiom we can understand now,

00:03:28.420 --> 00:03:31.790 align:middle line:84%
it felt more important than
ever to find a new language,

00:03:31.790 --> 00:03:33.520 align:middle line:84%
a new philosophy,
which has arisen

00:03:33.520 --> 00:03:35.890 align:middle line:84%
from the old, like everything
does-- and nothing's ever new,

00:03:35.890 --> 00:03:39.610 align:middle line:84%
really; it always arises
from what's gone before--

00:03:39.610 --> 00:03:43.280 align:middle line:84%
but which articulated
this perennial philosophy

00:03:43.280 --> 00:03:45.930 align:middle line:84%
in an evolved way,
an evolution of it,

00:03:45.930 --> 00:03:47.340 align:middle line:90%
so that we could really get it.

00:03:47.340 --> 00:03:50.430 align:middle line:90%
Because this really matters.

00:03:50.430 --> 00:03:52.510 align:middle line:84%
I really think that
there's something very

00:03:52.510 --> 00:03:54.230 align:middle line:84%
deep at the heart
of spirituality

00:03:54.230 --> 00:03:56.960 align:middle line:84%
which needs to come into
mainstream consciousness.

00:03:56.960 --> 00:03:59.780 align:middle line:84%
And the fact is that's
happening, but very slowly.

00:03:59.780 --> 00:04:01.730 align:middle line:84%
Still, it's kind of
in a mystical ghetto,

00:04:01.730 --> 00:04:03.970 align:middle line:84%
where people have kept
it alive for centuries.

00:04:03.970 --> 00:04:07.040 align:middle line:84%
And my passion is to say,
look, can we take this

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:09.181 align:middle line:90%
out into mainstream culture?

00:04:09.181 --> 00:04:10.480 align:middle line:84%
And to do that, I
think there's numbers

00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:12.670 align:middle line:90%
of things which have to happen.

00:04:12.670 --> 00:04:16.430 align:middle line:84%
The biggest obstacle
is spirituality itself.

00:04:16.430 --> 00:04:19.180 align:middle line:84%
It's not that everyone
else is stupid

00:04:19.180 --> 00:04:22.700 align:middle line:84%
or they haven't got
it or they're blind.

00:04:22.700 --> 00:04:23.940 align:middle line:84%
I don't think that's
what's going on.

00:04:23.940 --> 00:04:26.880 align:middle line:84%
I think what's going on is
that spirituality itself

00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:29.240 align:middle line:84%
needs to evolve
further so that it

00:04:29.240 --> 00:04:30.590 align:middle line:90%
can reach people more directly.

00:04:30.590 --> 00:04:31.610 align:middle line:90%
There's things wrong with it.

00:04:31.610 --> 00:04:33.850 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of modern
spirituality is very good,

00:04:33.850 --> 00:04:36.140 align:middle line:84%
but a lot it's also
very superstitious.

00:04:36.140 --> 00:04:39.020 align:middle line:84%
People who have come through
scientific background, or just

00:04:39.020 --> 00:04:40.470 align:middle line:84%
thinking people generally,
often look at it

00:04:40.470 --> 00:04:42.460 align:middle line:84%
and think, well, that's
a little bit nuts.

00:04:42.460 --> 00:04:44.150 align:middle line:84%
And the truth is,
it is a bit nuts.

00:04:44.150 --> 00:04:46.260 align:middle line:84%
And we need to get in there
and pull out what's nuts

00:04:46.260 --> 00:04:49.150 align:middle line:84%
and find the gem
which is at its heart.

00:04:49.150 --> 00:04:51.040 align:middle line:84%
And it needs to speak
to them on condition.

00:04:51.040 --> 00:04:53.510 align:middle line:84%
A lot of spirituality-- maybe
we can discuss this later as

00:04:53.510 --> 00:04:57.590 align:middle line:84%
well-- is rooted
in the past and is

00:04:57.590 --> 00:05:00.460 align:middle line:90%
fundamentally world-rejecting.

00:05:00.460 --> 00:05:02.390 align:middle line:84%
It's often been
created by celibate men

00:05:02.390 --> 00:05:05.380 align:middle line:84%
living in monasteries or in
caves, and it has that flavor.

00:05:05.380 --> 00:05:07.530 align:middle line:84%
So it's about pushing
the world away.

00:05:07.530 --> 00:05:10.060 align:middle line:84%
This is all an
illusion, rejection

00:05:10.060 --> 00:05:13.230 align:middle line:84%
of the personal, all
our personal attachments

00:05:13.230 --> 00:05:14.770 align:middle line:90%
and desires are all wrong.

00:05:14.770 --> 00:05:15.710 align:middle line:90%
We need to get rid of those.

00:05:15.710 --> 00:05:18.100 align:middle line:84%
And indeed, we need to get rid
of the whole personal self,

00:05:18.100 --> 00:05:19.890 align:middle line:90%
is wrong and is in the way.

00:05:19.890 --> 00:05:21.980 align:middle line:84%
In fact, often you hear
in spiritual circles

00:05:21.980 --> 00:05:24.180 align:middle line:84%
there's a little personal
self inside your head

00:05:24.180 --> 00:05:25.780 align:middle line:84%
who's out to get you
and stop you awakening.

00:05:25.780 --> 00:05:28.234 align:middle line:84%
It's like you've got the devil
inside going, no, no, no.

00:05:28.234 --> 00:05:29.100 align:middle line:90%
I don't want you to waken.

00:05:29.100 --> 00:05:33.260 align:middle line:84%
It's your ego trying to-- all of
this seems profoundly mistaken

00:05:33.260 --> 00:05:35.980 align:middle line:90%
to me and rooted in the past.

00:05:35.980 --> 00:05:38.230 align:middle line:84%
And the other big thing, which
is where your question came

00:05:38.230 --> 00:05:43.340 align:middle line:84%
from, is that 21st spirituality
needs to be congruent, needs

00:05:43.340 --> 00:05:45.970 align:middle line:84%
to be harmonious with
the awesome discoveries

00:05:45.970 --> 00:05:46.830 align:middle line:90%
of modern science.

00:05:46.830 --> 00:05:48.750 align:middle line:84%
Any form of spirituality
which cannot

00:05:48.750 --> 00:05:51.850 align:middle line:84%
be harmonious with modern
science is finished, I feel.

00:05:51.850 --> 00:05:54.440 align:middle line:10%
Or science needs to evolve,
because right now, there

00:05:54.440 --> 00:05:57.660 align:middle line:10%
is this whole science,
materialism science, that just

00:05:57.660 --> 00:06:00.660 align:middle line:10%
is no longer
matching the reality

00:06:00.660 --> 00:06:03.020 align:middle line:10%
and what we're finding
of the placebo effect

00:06:03.020 --> 00:06:07.300 align:middle line:10%
and of all the wonderful
things, the self-healing.

00:06:07.300 --> 00:06:11.810 align:middle line:84%
Well, one of the great
problems in human culture

00:06:11.810 --> 00:06:15.080 align:middle line:84%
with everything is
ideas tend to arise

00:06:15.080 --> 00:06:18.670 align:middle line:84%
with an inspired little
group of people who glimpse

00:06:18.670 --> 00:06:20.550 align:middle line:90%
into the depths of life.

00:06:20.550 --> 00:06:22.360 align:middle line:90%
And then the ideas spread.

00:06:22.360 --> 00:06:25.580 align:middle line:84%
As they spread, often they're
completely misunderstood.

00:06:25.580 --> 00:06:26.870 align:middle line:90%
You find this in religion.

00:06:26.870 --> 00:06:27.970 align:middle line:84%
I've written a
lot about religion

00:06:27.970 --> 00:06:32.160 align:middle line:84%
and how it misinterprets the
mystical heart of spirituality.

00:06:32.160 --> 00:06:34.090 align:middle line:84%
And the same thing has
happened in science.

00:06:34.090 --> 00:06:37.190 align:middle line:84%
If you go to the great
sages of spirituality,

00:06:37.190 --> 00:06:38.790 align:middle line:84%
they're saying
something very deep.

00:06:38.790 --> 00:06:42.330 align:middle line:84%
If you go to mass religion,
it's often very superficial.

00:06:42.330 --> 00:06:46.900 align:middle line:84%
In science, materialism, this
reductionism, as everything

00:06:46.900 --> 00:06:49.760 align:middle line:84%
can be reduced to matter--
this is what really exists,

00:06:49.760 --> 00:06:52.200 align:middle line:84%
and anything else
is just nonsense,

00:06:52.200 --> 00:06:56.690 align:middle line:84%
and really, it's all your genes,
and when you fall in love,

00:06:56.690 --> 00:06:59.120 align:middle line:84%
it's just chemicals, and
the birds are singing now

00:06:59.120 --> 00:07:01.070 align:middle line:84%
beautifully, but
really, it's just

00:07:01.070 --> 00:07:02.280 align:middle line:90%
their marking their territory.

00:07:02.280 --> 00:07:04.390 align:middle line:84%
And it's reducing everything,
the wonder of life

00:07:04.390 --> 00:07:07.230 align:middle line:84%
down, as if yes, yes, it
looks like it's wonderful,

00:07:07.230 --> 00:07:10.050 align:middle line:90%
but really it's just this.

00:07:10.050 --> 00:07:12.980 align:middle line:84%
That form of science
I feel has been

00:07:12.980 --> 00:07:15.420 align:middle line:90%
outdated for over 100 years.

00:07:15.420 --> 00:07:18.301 align:middle line:84%
In the mass mind generally,
people think that's science.

00:07:18.301 --> 00:07:19.000 align:middle line:90%
But it's not.

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:20.990 align:middle line:84%
A lot of scientists
think that's science.

00:07:20.990 --> 00:07:22.310 align:middle line:90%
But it's not.

00:07:22.310 --> 00:07:25.530 align:middle line:84%
What has happened
over 100 years ago

00:07:25.530 --> 00:07:28.930 align:middle line:84%
was that the physicists, the
people at the cutting edge,

00:07:28.930 --> 00:07:32.746 align:middle line:84%
have discovered that matter
doesn't really exist,

00:07:32.746 --> 00:07:37.290 align:middle line:84%
that this isn't here in the
way that we think it is at all.

00:07:37.290 --> 00:07:39.190 align:middle line:84%
Now once you've
reached that point,

00:07:39.190 --> 00:07:42.870 align:middle line:84%
and when you have the great
Nobel Prize winning physicists,

00:07:42.870 --> 00:07:45.720 align:middle line:84%
Niels Bohr, Einstein,
indeed, lots of them--

00:07:45.720 --> 00:07:47.520 align:middle line:84%
I quote them at
length in my book,

00:07:47.520 --> 00:07:50.390 align:middle line:84%
so they speak
themselves-- these people

00:07:50.390 --> 00:07:52.190 align:middle line:90%
are saying that that's finished.

00:07:52.190 --> 00:07:54.040 align:middle line:90%
That no longer makes any sense.

00:07:54.040 --> 00:07:56.710 align:middle line:84%
We need a whole new
paradigm for science

00:07:56.710 --> 00:07:58.430 align:middle line:90%
because of what we found.

00:07:58.430 --> 00:08:01.900 align:middle line:84%
So materialist science and
superficial spirituality

00:08:01.900 --> 00:08:03.470 align:middle line:90%
are never going to harmonize.

00:08:03.470 --> 00:08:07.250 align:middle line:84%
But this deep science and
this deep spirituality, these

00:08:07.250 --> 00:08:09.250 align:middle line:90%
are very natural bedfellows.

00:08:09.250 --> 00:08:12.600 align:middle line:84%
They really-- they're opposites,
but they co-exist perfectly.

00:08:12.600 --> 00:08:15.430 align:middle line:84%
And they express
the same insights

00:08:15.430 --> 00:08:17.580 align:middle line:90%
from opposite perspectives.

00:08:17.580 --> 00:08:19.150 align:middle line:90%
And that is quantum physics.

00:08:19.150 --> 00:08:20.890 align:middle line:84%
Quantum physics was the
big breakthrough, I think.

00:08:20.890 --> 00:08:26.800 align:middle line:84%
Again, misunderstood,
but incredibly profound

00:08:26.800 --> 00:08:28.680 align:middle line:90%
and mysterious.

00:08:28.680 --> 00:08:30.990 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things you find
in quantum physics which I find

00:08:30.990 --> 00:08:36.690 align:middle line:84%
really intriguing
is what it points

00:08:36.690 --> 00:08:40.360 align:middle line:84%
to is that the fundamental
nature of reality

00:08:40.360 --> 00:08:42.299 align:middle line:90%
is paradoxical.

00:08:42.299 --> 00:08:45.090 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is the very center of
the philosophy, which I explore

00:08:45.090 --> 00:08:48.160 align:middle line:84%
both in terms of harmonizing
science and spirituality,

00:08:48.160 --> 00:08:51.860 align:middle line:84%
but also in terms of your
personal awakening, actually

00:08:51.860 --> 00:08:53.820 align:middle line:84%
waking up to this
deep, awake state,

00:08:53.820 --> 00:08:57.930 align:middle line:84%
to a love of life and a
personal transformation.

00:08:57.930 --> 00:09:02.250 align:middle line:84%
And the center of my book,
"The Mystery Experience,"

00:09:02.250 --> 00:09:06.470 align:middle line:84%
is a new way of thinking,
which embraces paradox.

00:09:06.470 --> 00:09:09.540 align:middle line:84%
And I call it
paralogical thinking.

00:09:09.540 --> 00:09:11.770 align:middle line:84%
And the idea of
paralogical thinking

00:09:11.770 --> 00:09:16.760 align:middle line:84%
is that a paradox is not a
problem to be solved always,

00:09:16.760 --> 00:09:20.780 align:middle line:84%
that when you get down to the
depths of life, a paradox,

00:09:20.780 --> 00:09:23.920 align:middle line:84%
or what I call a paradoxity,
is actually the solution.

00:09:23.920 --> 00:09:26.070 align:middle line:84%
When you reach the
paradox, you've actually

00:09:26.070 --> 00:09:29.353 align:middle line:84%
found what you're looking for.
Now--

00:09:29.353 --> 00:09:30.560 align:middle line:90%
Give us an example here.

00:09:30.560 --> 00:09:31.260 align:middle line:90%
OK, OK.

00:09:31.260 --> 00:09:33.170 align:middle line:84%
So-- well, let me just
tell you about heritage

00:09:33.170 --> 00:09:35.520 align:middle line:84%
of that idea for a
moment, because I

00:09:35.520 --> 00:09:37.220 align:middle line:90%
framed it in a very new way.

00:09:37.220 --> 00:09:39.155 align:middle line:84%
And hopefully in the
book, it's comes alive.

00:09:39.155 --> 00:09:41.760 align:middle line:84%
And it's something that
you can apply everywhere.

00:09:41.760 --> 00:09:42.990 align:middle line:84%
Once you've got
it, you just find--

00:09:42.990 --> 00:09:46.640 align:middle line:84%
ooh, ooh, ooh-- everywhere
you look there's this paradox.

00:09:46.640 --> 00:09:47.510 align:middle line:90%
But it's an old idea.

00:09:47.510 --> 00:09:49.660 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can go
back to ancient China

00:09:49.660 --> 00:09:52.620 align:middle line:84%
with the idea of the Tao,
which is the mystery of life,

00:09:52.620 --> 00:09:54.910 align:middle line:90%
is rising as yin and yang.

00:09:54.910 --> 00:09:57.010 align:middle line:84%
Most people are familiar
with the yin and yang sign.

00:09:57.010 --> 00:10:00.220 align:middle line:84%
You've got the black and the
white, and they're in movement,

00:10:00.220 --> 00:10:01.420 align:middle line:90%
and one contains the other.

00:10:01.420 --> 00:10:02.940 align:middle line:84%
There's a little dot
of black in the white

00:10:02.940 --> 00:10:04.940 align:middle line:84%
and a little dot of
white in the black.

00:10:04.940 --> 00:10:10.650 align:middle line:84%
And life is this paradox in
which the opposites co-exist.

00:10:10.650 --> 00:10:13.390 align:middle line:84%
You can also see it in the
ideas of Plato and Socrates,

00:10:13.390 --> 00:10:14.530 align:middle line:90%
in the dialectics.

00:10:14.530 --> 00:10:17.490 align:middle line:84%
You can see it right-- in
fact, I would say that it's

00:10:17.490 --> 00:10:19.390 align:middle line:84%
one of the most fundamental
ideas underlying

00:10:19.390 --> 00:10:21.950 align:middle line:84%
the whole of Western
philosophy, arising in Hegel--

00:10:21.950 --> 00:10:24.000 align:middle line:90%
just over and over again.

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:27.110 align:middle line:84%
Life is paradoxical, and
when you reach the depths,

00:10:27.110 --> 00:10:29.530 align:middle line:90%
the opposites coexist.

00:10:29.530 --> 00:10:31.170 align:middle line:84%
Now, what I find
fascinating is then

00:10:31.170 --> 00:10:33.120 align:middle line:84%
you come to the
quantum physicists,

00:10:33.120 --> 00:10:35.290 align:middle line:90%
and they found the same thing.

00:10:35.290 --> 00:10:38.130 align:middle line:84%
When they were looking at the
fundamental nature of this--

00:10:38.130 --> 00:10:42.290 align:middle line:84%
I mean light, actually,
the thing which illuminates

00:10:42.290 --> 00:10:44.750 align:middle line:90%
everything but you can't see.

00:10:44.750 --> 00:10:46.690 align:middle line:90%
How's that for a paradox?

00:10:46.690 --> 00:10:48.310 align:middle line:90%
What is its nature?

00:10:48.310 --> 00:10:51.470 align:middle line:84%
And what they found
was that if you set up

00:10:51.470 --> 00:10:54.880 align:middle line:84%
an experiment in a certain way,
light appears to be made up

00:10:54.880 --> 00:10:57.790 align:middle line:90%
of little discrete particles.

00:10:57.790 --> 00:10:59.420 align:middle line:84%
But if you set it up
in a different way,

00:10:59.420 --> 00:11:02.640 align:middle line:90%
light appears to be one wave.

00:11:02.640 --> 00:11:04.021 align:middle line:84%
So they were faced
with, which is it?

00:11:04.021 --> 00:11:05.380 align:middle line:84%
Is it a wave?
Is it a particle?

00:11:05.380 --> 00:11:09.140 align:middle line:84%
Now, logical thinking is
based on it's either this

00:11:09.140 --> 00:11:10.720 align:middle line:90%
or it's not this.

00:11:10.720 --> 00:11:12.200 align:middle line:90%
So it's one or the other.

00:11:12.200 --> 00:11:13.440 align:middle line:90%
That's how we think logically.

00:11:13.440 --> 00:11:17.320 align:middle line:84%
And for most purposes,
logical thinking is fantastic.

00:11:17.320 --> 00:11:18.470 align:middle line:90%
I'm a big fan.

00:11:18.470 --> 00:11:20.550 align:middle line:90%
We should be more logical.

00:11:20.550 --> 00:11:22.180 align:middle line:84%
A lot of spirituality
is illogical,

00:11:22.180 --> 00:11:24.280 align:middle line:90%
and it drives me nuts.

00:11:24.280 --> 00:11:26.060 align:middle line:90%
But that's another video.

00:11:26.060 --> 00:11:27.390 align:middle line:90%
But that's another discussion.

00:11:27.390 --> 00:11:28.810 align:middle line:90%
But it does.

00:11:28.810 --> 00:11:31.490 align:middle line:84%
So I want to make it clear that
I've got nothing against logic.

00:11:31.490 --> 00:11:34.210 align:middle line:90%
We need it-- on the surface.

00:11:34.210 --> 00:11:36.350 align:middle line:84%
But if you want to understand
the depths of life,

00:11:36.350 --> 00:11:38.920 align:middle line:84%
you need to think
paralogically, which

00:11:38.920 --> 00:11:42.290 align:middle line:84%
means you can see, as the
quantum physicists discovered,

00:11:42.290 --> 00:11:45.750 align:middle line:84%
that at the depths, you can
see things in opposite ways,

00:11:45.750 --> 00:11:47.360 align:middle line:90%
and they're both true.

00:11:47.360 --> 00:11:48.710 align:middle line:84%
So they came to the
conclusion, look,

00:11:48.710 --> 00:11:51.390 align:middle line:84%
it's both a wave and
a particle, depending

00:11:51.390 --> 00:11:53.560 align:middle line:90%
on how you look at it.

00:11:53.560 --> 00:11:57.000 align:middle line:84%
And Niels Bohr, one of the
pioneers of quantum physics,

00:11:57.000 --> 00:12:02.280 align:middle line:84%
Nobel Prize winner, great man,
he actually took the yin yang

00:12:02.280 --> 00:12:05.090 align:middle line:84%
sign, the ancient symbol, and
stuck it on his coat of arms

00:12:05.090 --> 00:12:08.130 align:middle line:84%
when he designed it,
and put underneath it

00:12:08.130 --> 00:12:09.980 align:middle line:84%
"The opposites are
complementary."

00:12:09.980 --> 00:12:14.250 align:middle line:84%
That's a direct echo
back to ancient Taoism.

00:12:14.250 --> 00:12:15.420 align:middle line:90%
Because that's what he's found.

00:12:15.420 --> 00:12:17.020 align:middle line:84%
He'd found the
opposites co-exist.

00:12:17.020 --> 00:12:20.450 align:middle line:90%


00:12:20.450 --> 00:12:23.500 align:middle line:84%
Now, the implications of this--
well, let me quote Niels Bohr,

00:12:23.500 --> 00:12:26.080 align:middle line:90%
again because I'm a fan.

00:12:26.080 --> 00:12:29.140 align:middle line:84%
He said, if you're looking at
trivial truths, what I would

00:12:29.140 --> 00:12:33.430 align:middle line:84%
call surface truths, the
opposite of something

00:12:33.430 --> 00:12:35.210 align:middle line:90%
which is true is false.

00:12:35.210 --> 00:12:36.000 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:37.000 align:middle line:90%
That's logic.

00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:41.100 align:middle line:84%
But if you want to understand
deep truths, he said,

00:12:41.100 --> 00:12:45.060 align:middle line:84%
the opposite of a deep
truth is also true.

00:12:45.060 --> 00:12:47.190 align:middle line:84%
Now, that flies in
the face of logic,

00:12:47.190 --> 00:12:50.640 align:middle line:84%
but if we think paralogically,
we can start to understand, ah,

00:12:50.640 --> 00:12:53.160 align:middle line:84%
right, so when we
find the paradox,

00:12:53.160 --> 00:12:56.710 align:middle line:84%
we're seeing the nature
of reality from two

00:12:56.710 --> 00:12:59.080 align:middle line:84%
but opposite
perspectives at once.

00:12:59.080 --> 00:13:01.060 align:middle line:84%
Now, let me give
you some examples.

00:13:01.060 --> 00:13:04.400 align:middle line:84%
Well, let's deal with them
coming through science

00:13:04.400 --> 00:13:06.530 align:middle line:90%
and spirituality straight off.

00:13:06.530 --> 00:13:08.850 align:middle line:84%
They're a paralogical pair--
deep science I'm talking

00:13:08.850 --> 00:13:10.340 align:middle line:90%
about and deep spirituality.

00:13:10.340 --> 00:13:13.670 align:middle line:84%
Deep science looks outwards
into the objective world.

00:13:13.670 --> 00:13:16.380 align:middle line:84%
It's an objective
investigation, which goes,

00:13:16.380 --> 00:13:18.430 align:middle line:90%
what are these appearances?

00:13:18.430 --> 00:13:21.810 align:middle line:84%
There's this incredible
pageant of colors and shapes

00:13:21.810 --> 00:13:24.510 align:middle line:90%
and sounds, and what is it?

00:13:24.510 --> 00:13:26.280 align:middle line:84%
And it started off by
going, well, there it is.

00:13:26.280 --> 00:13:26.980 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:13:26.980 --> 00:13:30.540 align:middle line:84%
And it looked into it, and
the more it looked into it,

00:13:30.540 --> 00:13:34.590 align:middle line:84%
the more it found that what it
appeared to be on the surface

00:13:34.590 --> 00:13:39.130 align:middle line:84%
was the opposite of what it
was underneath the surface.

00:13:39.130 --> 00:13:42.071 align:middle line:84%
So on the surface, this is a
physical object, very tangible.

00:13:42.071 --> 00:13:44.620 align:middle line:84%
It's real.
And to deny that is crazy.

00:13:44.620 --> 00:13:46.510 align:middle line:84%
You'd literally go
nuts, wouldn't you?

00:13:46.510 --> 00:13:47.520 align:middle line:90%
I'm holding a mic with it.

00:13:47.520 --> 00:13:49.391 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, right, yeah--
all of this, everything.

00:13:49.391 --> 00:13:52.500 align:middle line:84%
Right.
You, me, is ahh!

00:13:52.500 --> 00:13:58.740 align:middle line:84%
But we now know that
99.999999999990%--

00:13:58.740 --> 00:14:02.580 align:middle line:84%
a lot-- is nothing.
It's empty space.

00:14:02.580 --> 00:14:04.420 align:middle line:84%
Like the universe is
mostly empty space.

00:14:04.420 --> 00:14:08.400 align:middle line:84%
When you come into the subatomic
world, it's just not there.

00:14:08.400 --> 00:14:10.190 align:middle line:90%
So here's a paradox.

00:14:10.190 --> 00:14:14.070 align:middle line:84%
My hand is both there,
and it is not there.

00:14:14.070 --> 00:14:15.230 align:middle line:90%
Which is true?

00:14:15.230 --> 00:14:16.670 align:middle line:90%
Well, they're both true.

00:14:16.670 --> 00:14:19.700 align:middle line:84%
Now, for living on the
surface in the world of logic,

00:14:19.700 --> 00:14:22.510 align:middle line:90%
either/or logic, it's there.

00:14:22.510 --> 00:14:25.360 align:middle line:84%
But if you want to understand
the depths, you have to go,

00:14:25.360 --> 00:14:27.040 align:middle line:90%
and it's also not there.

00:14:27.040 --> 00:14:28.160 align:middle line:90%
Hm.

00:14:28.160 --> 00:14:29.420 align:middle line:90%
That's interesting.

00:14:29.420 --> 00:14:32.140 align:middle line:84%
How does that change
my consciousness?

00:14:32.140 --> 00:14:34.190 align:middle line:84%
If I look at my hand,
if I look at you and go,

00:14:34.190 --> 00:14:35.890 align:middle line:84%
ooh, you're there
and you're not there.

00:14:35.890 --> 00:14:38.460 align:middle line:90%
And I'm here and I'm not here.

00:14:38.460 --> 00:14:39.700 align:middle line:90%
And both are true.

00:14:39.700 --> 00:14:45.720 align:middle line:84%
And can I see those two
perspectives at once?

00:14:45.720 --> 00:14:48.190 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we're doing when
we're thinking paralogically.

00:14:48.190 --> 00:14:50.530 align:middle line:84%
So science has gone out
and gone, ooh, look,

00:14:50.530 --> 00:14:52.280 align:middle line:84%
it seems like it's there
and it's not there,

00:14:52.280 --> 00:14:54.220 align:middle line:90%
into the objective world.

00:14:54.220 --> 00:14:56.940 align:middle line:84%
Well, spirituality,
deep spirituality,

00:14:56.940 --> 00:14:59.500 align:middle line:84%
is the paralogical
complement of that.

00:14:59.500 --> 00:15:02.180 align:middle line:84%
What it does is it goes
in the opposite direction.

00:15:02.180 --> 00:15:04.830 align:middle line:84%
Here we are sitting in
this beautiful graveyard,

00:15:04.830 --> 00:15:06.330 align:middle line:90%
full of all these appearances.

00:15:06.330 --> 00:15:08.600 align:middle line:84%
Science goes, what
are the appearances?

00:15:08.600 --> 00:15:12.670 align:middle line:84%
Spirituality goes,
who's looking at them?

00:15:12.670 --> 00:15:14.340 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
essential difference.

00:15:14.340 --> 00:15:15.050 align:middle line:90%
What are these?

00:15:15.050 --> 00:15:17.530 align:middle line:90%
This is spirituality-- who am I?

00:15:17.530 --> 00:15:20.420 align:middle line:84%
What is it that's
experiencing this?

00:15:20.420 --> 00:15:23.860 align:middle line:84%
So it makes the journey
inward, if you like.

00:15:23.860 --> 00:15:25.680 align:middle line:84%
It comes this way.
Who's looking?

00:15:25.680 --> 00:15:26.540 align:middle line:90%
Who's looking?

00:15:26.540 --> 00:15:31.020 align:middle line:84%
And as you go inward, you appear
to be this body on the surface,

00:15:31.020 --> 00:15:33.190 align:middle line:84%
and then there's,
well, what else am I?

00:15:33.190 --> 00:15:34.600 align:middle line:84%
And the very first
thing you discover,

00:15:34.600 --> 00:15:37.800 align:middle line:84%
which is pretty obvious,
is you're not just a body.

00:15:37.800 --> 00:15:41.900 align:middle line:84%
You discover that you're
also a soul or a psyche.

00:15:41.900 --> 00:15:42.940 align:middle line:90%
The word psyche is Greek.

00:15:42.940 --> 00:15:44.130 align:middle line:90%
It just means soul.

00:15:44.130 --> 00:15:45.820 align:middle line:84%
And you come back into
yourself, and there's

00:15:45.820 --> 00:15:49.180 align:middle line:84%
another whole subjective
world of the psyche, where

00:15:49.180 --> 00:15:51.190 align:middle line:84%
there's all these
imaginations, thoughts

00:15:51.190 --> 00:15:53.650 align:middle line:90%
and images and feelings.

00:15:53.650 --> 00:15:54.720 align:middle line:90%
And it's an endless world.

00:15:54.720 --> 00:15:56.690 align:middle line:84%
You turn your attention
into it, and it goes,

00:15:56.690 --> 00:15:58.710 align:middle line:90%
it's as infinite as this world.

00:15:58.710 --> 00:16:00.190 align:middle line:90%
You can explore it forever.

00:16:00.190 --> 00:16:02.090 align:middle line:84%
And I've done a lot,
and you can just

00:16:02.090 --> 00:16:05.750 align:middle line:84%
go on and on and on-- and
archetypes and the world

00:16:05.750 --> 00:16:07.730 align:middle line:90%
of psychology.

00:16:07.730 --> 00:16:08.620 align:middle line:90%
But it's not in space.

00:16:08.620 --> 00:16:11.040 align:middle line:90%
Where is it?

00:16:11.040 --> 00:16:12.950 align:middle line:84%
We are sitting
here-- apart from me,

00:16:12.950 --> 00:16:15.060 align:middle line:84%
because I jump about and move
my arms-- but you're being--

00:16:15.060 --> 00:16:17.070 align:middle line:90%
[BOTH LAUGHING]

00:16:17.070 --> 00:16:20.320 align:middle line:84%
We're essentially-- the
bodies are just sitting here.

00:16:20.320 --> 00:16:22.770 align:middle line:84%
And the action is
all taking place

00:16:22.770 --> 00:16:26.080 align:middle line:84%
in the psyche, in the soul,
of this world of ideas.

00:16:26.080 --> 00:16:27.180 align:middle line:84%
That's where we're
communicating.

00:16:27.180 --> 00:16:29.720 align:middle line:90%
So here's my body and your body.

00:16:29.720 --> 00:16:32.970 align:middle line:84%
And then through this vibration
in the air of these symbols,

00:16:32.970 --> 00:16:34.490 align:middle line:84%
these words, this--
[BLOWS OUT]--

00:16:34.490 --> 00:16:39.350 align:middle line:84%
reaching across to your
ear, this psyche, this soul,

00:16:39.350 --> 00:16:42.400 align:middle line:84%
which is not in space--
where is it?-- is

00:16:42.400 --> 00:16:44.210 align:middle line:90%
communicating with another one.

00:16:44.210 --> 00:16:45.350 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:16:45.350 --> 00:16:46.497 align:middle line:90%
That's pretty interesting.

00:16:46.497 --> 00:16:47.780 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:16:47.780 --> 00:16:49.891 align:middle line:84%
That takes the conversation
to a whole other level, yes.

00:16:49.891 --> 00:16:50.590 align:middle line:90%
OK, right.

00:16:50.590 --> 00:16:55.160 align:middle line:84%
So through these
forms, material forms,

00:16:55.160 --> 00:16:57.880 align:middle line:84%
something which has
no material existence

00:16:57.880 --> 00:16:59.280 align:middle line:84%
is connecting with
something which

00:16:59.280 --> 00:17:01.880 align:middle line:90%
has no material existence.

00:17:01.880 --> 00:17:02.830 align:middle line:90%
And then you keep going.

00:17:02.830 --> 00:17:05.540 align:middle line:84%
OK, so all right, so I'm
witnessing right now,

00:17:05.540 --> 00:17:08.390 align:middle line:84%
I'm witnessing my body,
this world of matter

00:17:08.390 --> 00:17:11.359 align:middle line:84%
and the sensation, and I'm
wielding this other world

00:17:11.359 --> 00:17:12.960 align:middle line:90%
of imagination.

00:17:12.960 --> 00:17:15.040 align:middle line:84%
Well, there's a
paradoxity for a start.

00:17:15.040 --> 00:17:16.940 align:middle line:84%
So what I'm witnessing
is a paradox.

00:17:16.940 --> 00:17:22.120 align:middle line:84%
It's both material and abstract,
immaterial, at the same time.

00:17:22.120 --> 00:17:25.150 align:middle line:84%
Which is it?
Well, it's both.

00:17:25.150 --> 00:17:28.390 align:middle line:84%
Now I'm still left with,
well, who's looking?

00:17:28.390 --> 00:17:30.490 align:middle line:84%
Who is it that's
experiencing both

00:17:30.490 --> 00:17:33.650 align:middle line:90%
the sensation and the thoughts?

00:17:33.650 --> 00:17:35.100 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:17:35.100 --> 00:17:38.460 align:middle line:84%
What is that being,
which is always there,

00:17:38.460 --> 00:17:42.330 align:middle line:84%
which is witnessing Tim doing
this, witnessing the thoughts

00:17:42.330 --> 00:17:45.650 align:middle line:84%
in my mind, witnessing you
nodding, witnessing the birds

00:17:45.650 --> 00:17:47.000 align:middle line:90%
singing.

00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:49.950 align:middle line:84%
And that's the essence
of deep spirituality,

00:17:49.950 --> 00:17:53.040 align:middle line:90%
is finding your being.

00:17:53.040 --> 00:17:57.080 align:middle line:84%
The word "spirit" really
points to your being.

00:17:57.080 --> 00:17:58.250 align:middle line:90%
"Spirit" means "essence."

00:17:58.250 --> 00:17:59.640 align:middle line:90%
It's an old-fashioned word.

00:17:59.640 --> 00:18:01.110 align:middle line:84%
It's a difficult word,
"spirit," because you

00:18:01.110 --> 00:18:02.800 align:middle line:84%
get this idea of a
spirit being some sort

00:18:02.800 --> 00:18:04.710 align:middle line:90%
of ghouly, ghosty thing.

00:18:04.710 --> 00:18:08.600 align:middle line:84%
But it's really pointing to
your being, your essence.

00:18:08.600 --> 00:18:10.460 align:middle line:84%
"Essence" comes from
"essay," "to be."

00:18:10.460 --> 00:18:11.630 align:middle line:90%
It's your being.

00:18:11.630 --> 00:18:13.530 align:middle line:84%
So what is your being?
What is it you are?

00:18:13.530 --> 00:18:18.520 align:middle line:84%
What is that thing you call "I"
that is witnessing all of this?

00:18:18.520 --> 00:18:24.440 align:middle line:84%
So the journey in takes you
to this mysterious presence

00:18:24.440 --> 00:18:29.810 align:middle line:84%
within which all of these
experiences are arising.

00:18:29.810 --> 00:18:33.290 align:middle line:84%
Now, how we match those
two insights it's together

00:18:33.290 --> 00:18:34.700 align:middle line:90%
is the challenge.

00:18:34.700 --> 00:18:35.400 align:middle line:90%
And I think we can.

00:18:35.400 --> 00:18:37.140 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
Tell us.

